Manchester City Routs Rival United 6-1 in English Premier League

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-10-23T14:27:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/manchester-city-routs-rival-united-6-1-in-english-premier-league.html
Manchester City beat Manchester
United 6-1 to strengthen its lead at the top of the standings in
the English Premier League.  Mario Balotelli  and Edin Dzeko each scored twice at Old
Trafford as City moved five points ahead of its rival. Sergio
Aguero and  David Silva  added one goal each as City scored five
times in the second half after United’s Jonny Evans was red-
carded.  Arsenal beat Stoke 3-1, while Everton won by the same score
at Fulham in today’s other early matches. Tottenham is at
Blackburn and QPR hosts Chelsea later.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  